interactions.flavorLineOne:
Ada-1 feels inspired… by a Guardian, by you. The Black Armory can begin to stand on its own feet once again, and it's all thanks to your efforts. Ada-1's gain is also your own, as there are many more Black Armory weapons to craft and wield. 

Visit Ada-1 to obtain new weapon frames for crafting Black Armory gear.

Ada-1 has started to see the world differently. A Guardian, of all people, was the one to rekindle the flame of her determination, which she had buried so deep for so long.

Return to Ada-1 to get new weapon frames for the recently discovered Izanami Forge and craft more Black Armory weapons.

Ada-1's head is spinning with all of these Guardians associating with the Black Armory, but rest assured, she is very pleased. Your burgeoning relationship with her is beginning to bear fruit.

Visit Ada-1 to get new weapon frames for the recently discovered Gofannon Forge and craft new Black Armory weapons.

This isn't a gun, but a charged Hyperion Core that, according to the Black Armory Papers, is made to enhance a weapon very dear to Ada-1. She assembles it.

This weapon is now a key to the last secret that the Black Armory holds.

Your thoroughness in assisting the Black Armory has borne fruit. You have helped Ada-1 unlock secrets hidden away in her subconscious mind.

Great Job!

The decryption device allowed Ada-1 to decipher pages of the Black Armory Papers. She discovered instructions for an unidentified frame—maybe for a new Black Armory weapon.

Follow Ada-1's instructions to collect some unusual and hard-to-find materials for the Unidentified Frame.

The Black Armory's vault has been recovered, and along with it, the Black Armory Papers—the personal journals of Henriette Meyrin. Unfortunately, Siviks got to them first and tore out many of the pages. Ada-1 insists that you find them all and return them to her, so that the journals may be whole once again.

Complete Fallen forge ignitions to retrieve the missing pages from the Kell's Scourge.
Ada-1 infuses the Calibrated Frame with the Radiant Matrix to create the Radiant Frame.

Ada-1 is surprised by what you have accomplished with the weapon frame. She now sees a potential within you that she knows would be foolish not to develop. The calibrated weapon frame is just one step toward helping the Black Armory. Another is finding the lost forge, which Ada-1 believes to be hidden deep within the Cabal base in the EDZ.

Travel to the EDZ and locate the missing Volundr Forge to craft the Black Armory weapon.
Ada-1 infuses the Calibrated Frame with the Radiant Matrix to create the Radiant Frame.

With the discovery of the Izanami Forge on the Exodus Black, Ada-1 now believes there could be even more lost forges to reclaim. But first, the Izanami Forge needs to be reignited.

Gather the necessary components to repair the broken igniter.

Ada-1 notes you've collected almost all the proper components to fully repair the igniter. But… one special component is missing.

Complete an advanced version of "The Insight Terminus" to complete the Izanami Forge igniter.
Ada-1 infuses the Calibrated Frame with the Radiant Matrix to create the Radiant Frame.

Due to the Red War, the Black Armory lost access to its forge in the EDZ. Since then, Ada-1 has been unable to locate it herself.

Though she continues to distrust Guardians, Ada-1 hands you a weapon frame in case you manage to locate the Volundr Forge. With this frame, you will eventually be able to craft a Black Armory weapon—but first you must calibrate it and bring it back to Ada-1.

Follow the steps to calibrate the weapon frame.
Ada-1 infuses the Calibrated Frame with the Radiant Matrix to create the Radiant Frame.

Ada-1 is stunned by the Guardians' discovery—a secret Black Armory facility known as Niobe Labs, lost since the Golden Age. Within it, a mold for a key was found. Ada-1 passes it to you, trusting that you can discover its purpose.

Ada-1 urges you to search the facility and further unearth its secrets.

Ada-1 has realized that the Black Armory gear has been tainted by the Fallen, and it does not appear to come from the Volundr Forge. She believes the Spider may have more information.

Collect more of the Fallen tainted gear in the Tangled Shore to convince the Spider to help you find who's behind it.

Due to the Red War, the Black Armory lost access to its forge in the EDZ. Since then, Ada-1 has been unable to locate it herself.

Though she continues to distrust Guardians, Ada-1 hands you a weapon frame in case you manage to locate the Volundr Forge. With this frame, you will eventually be able to craft a Black Armory weapon—but first you must calibrate it and bring it back to Ada-1.

Follow the steps to calibrate the weapon frame.
